{{Orphan|date=June 2015}}
The '''Virgocentric flow''' (VCF) is the preferred movement of [[Local Group]] [[galaxy|galaxies]] towards the [[Virgo cluster]]<ref name="Chernin2010">{{cite journal | last=Chernin | first=A. D. | author2=Karachentsev, I. D. | author3=Nasonova, O. G. | author4=Teerikorpi, P. | author5=Valtonen, M. J. | author6=Dolgachev, V. P. | author7=Domozhilova, L. M. | author8=Byrd, G. G. | display-authors=3 | date = September 2010 | title = Dark energy domination in the Virgocentric flow | url = http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/bib_query?arXiv:1006.0555 | arxiv = 1006.0555 | journal = Astronomy and Astrophysics | volume = 520 | pages = id.A104 | bibcode = 2010A&A...520A.104C | doi = 10.1051/0004-6361/201014912 | accessdate = 30 November 2014 }}</ref> caused by its overwhelming [[gravitation|gravity]], which separates [[Gravitational binding energy|bound]] objects from the [[Hubble's law|Hubble flow]] of [[Metric expansion of space|cosmic expansion]]. The VCF can refer to the Local Group's movement towards the [[Virgo Supercluster|Virgo ''Super''cluster]],<ref name="Yahil1986">{{cite book |last=Yahil |first=Amos |editor1-last=Madore|editor1-first=Barry F. |editor1-link=Barry F. Madore |editor2-last=Tully|editor2-first=R. Breant |editor2-link=R. Brent Tully |date=1986 |title=Galaxy Distances and Deviations from Universal Expansion |series=NATO ASI Series |chapter=Is the Criticism of the Virgocentric Flow Model Justified? |url=https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-94-009-4702-3_26 |publisher=Springer Netherlands |pages=143–145 |doi=10.1007/978-94-009-4702-3_26 |isbn=978-94-009-4702-3 |accessdate=30 November 2014 }}</ref> since its center is considered synonymous with the Virgo cluster, but more tedious to ascertain due to its much larger volume. The excess velocity of Local Group galaxies towards, and with respect to, the Virgo Cluster are 100 to 400&nbsp;km/s.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Virgo Cluster of Galaxies |url=http://messier.seds.org/more/virgo.html}}</ref> This excess velocity is referred to as each galaxy's [[peculiar velocity]].
